7 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Veterans Affairs; amending 62 O.S. 2021, Sections
9 34.48, 34.57, 34.64, and 34.80, which relate to
federal funds, agency clearing accounts, payment of
10 claims or payrolls, and records of warrants, checks,
or orders by the Office of Management and Enterprise
11 Services; defining term; exempting certain federal
funds administered by the Oklahoma Department of
12 Veterans Affairs from certain provisions; creating
the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs Federally
13 Funded Veteran Care Enterprise Fund; requiring the
Department to maintain certain records; requiring the
14 Department to electronically submit certain reports;
requiring the Department to remain subject to certain
15 examinations; exempting certain patient-pay monies
received by the Department from certain requirements;
16 construing provisions; authorizing the Department to
establish and administer certain procedures;
17 establishing certain requirements for certain
procedures; exempting certain funds from certain
18 filing or certification requirements; transferring
certain funds to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
19 Affairs Revolving Fund; amending 72 O.S. 2021,
Section 222, as amended by Section 2, Chapter 42,
20 O.S.L. 2024 (72 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 222), which
relates to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
21 Affairs Revolving Fund; allowing certain funds to be
deposited into certain accounts by the Department;
22 requiring certain records to be subject to audit;
creating the Oklahoma Veterans Assistance Fund;
23 removing certain requirement to transfer certain
funds; allowing certain expenditures to be kept in
24 certain fund; exempting certain monies from certain
Req. No. 3575 Page 1

1 fiscal year limitations; establishing certain
requirements for certain funds to be withdrawn;
2 amending 74 O.S. 2021, Section 85.12, as amended by
Section 2, Chapter 339, O.S.L. 2023 (74 O.S. Supp.
3 2025, Section 85.12), which relates to act not to
affect nonconflicting procedures; exempting certain
4 purchase of goods and services by the Department from
